a three-hour secret meeting between President Uhuru Kenyatta and former prime minister Raila Odinga on Wednesday night followed by a daylong inspection tour of government projects by the duo appears to have lowered tension and speculation over the handshake and building bridges initiative. although the two handshake principals avoided commenting on politics, their body language and Odinga's resolve to support government projects might be the clearest indication yet to their supporters that all is well. KTN news senior political affairs reporter Chris thairu reports.